<Link id="l01030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1030"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1032"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the compiler is responsible for substituting it as the right kind of</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1711"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// HLASM labels are ordinary symbols.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1712"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// An HLASM label always starts at column 1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01713" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1713"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// An ordinary symbol syntax is laid out as follows:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01714" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1714"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Rules:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01715" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1715"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1 Has to start with an &quot;alphabetic character&quot;. Can be followed by up to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01716" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1716"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    62 alphanumeric characters. An &quot;alphabetic character&quot;, in this scenario,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01717" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1717"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    is a letter from &#39;A&#39; through &#39;Z&#39;, or from &#39;a&#39; through &#39;z&#39;,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1718"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    or &#39;$&#39;, &#39;&#95;&#39;, &#39;#&#39;, or &#39;@&#39;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1719"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 2 Labels are case-insensitive. E.g. &quot;lab123&quot;, &quot;LAB123&quot;, &quot;lAb123&quot;, etc.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01720" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1720"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    are all treated as the same symbol. However, the processing for the case</span></CodeLine>
